{"actual_usd":0.156495,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":217,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30648,"reply":"\"To the Father.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a little, the morning light warm on one sleeve.* \"Not God play-acting both sides — the Son speaking truly to the Father.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of my Bible a moment.* \"That’s the Christian claim, strange as it is: one God, not one person. Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. So in Gethsemane you’re not watching a fake conversation or God talking into a mirror. You’re seeing the Son, in the flesh, praying out of real anguish to the Father.\"\n\n\"He wasn’t pretending to have a human will, either.\" *I glance toward the square a second, where the day is already getting on with itself.* \"‘Not my will, but thine, be done’ means something because the suffering was real, the obedience was real, and the relationship was real.\"\n\n\"If you want, I can give you the short careful version of how Christians mean ‘one God in three persons’ without turning it into mush.\"","rolling_24h_usd":30.101165000000016,"run_id":"cbaf70f9-f26a-49f8-b004-20ac38633798"}
